channel.title: Confused
channel.description:
Been working on a project for about 2 and a half months, and decided to host it off my computer for a few days so my friends can find bugs. I came home from work today and tried logging in, and it wouldn't let me login on my personal client. my friends cannot connect either tho when I released it to them I had 13 of them online for like 5 hours before I went to bed. I checked my portforwarding, restarted server and then restarted my computer, and I still haven't found out why the hell it's not letting anyone login? All it says on login attempt is "error connecting to server" Can someone add me on skype, I have a microphone and I can screenshare my problem and explain to the best of my knowledge whats happening.
Skype name Nick.Cholka

item.title: Confused
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

Sounds like you have a deadlocking issue.

http://run-server.org/runescape-development/google/snippets/290951-pi-deadlock-issue-fix.html
(Add an ‘e’ to the end of ‘run’)
